Imagine your fintech company has an internal dashboard used by customer support agents at a physical office in Bengaluru. An agent clicks a button to retrieve a customer's highly sensitive transaction history to resolve a payment dispute.

Here is the exact, step-by-step flow of how that click travels through every service in your Zero-Trust architecture.

Step 1: The Secure Entry (On-Premises to AWS)

The agent clicks "Fetch Transactions." The request leaves their laptop, but it never touches the public internet.

Site-to-Site VPN / Direct Connect: The request travels from the corporate office router through a dedicated, encrypted private tunnel directly into AWS.


AWS Transit Gateway : The request arrives at the Transit Gateway, the central "post office." The Transit Gateway checks its routing tables and forwards the traffic specifically into your strictly private fintech-zero-trust-vpc.

